                           29. In this study, we only observed GC as a monovalent alcohol (four electron reductant) and glyoxylic acid (GO) as a monovalent aldehyde (two electron reductant). For optimization of the catalytic performances on the PEAEC, we conducted controlled-potential electrolysis by changing various conditions, e.g., temperature (25–70 °C), OX concentration (0.01–1 M), flow rate (0.1–1.0 ml min−1), reaction area (1–25 cm2), amount of IrO2 catalyst (1–10 mg cm−2), and cathode electrode (TiO2/Ti-M or TiO2/Ti-F).
